definitions.definition: An area around the end of a bridge.
A fortification around the end of a bridge .
An area of ground on the enemy 's side of a river or other obstacle , especially one that needs to be taken and defended in order to secure an advance .
Either of the two atoms in different parts of a molecule that are connected by a bridge of two or more other atoms

main_definition: An area around the end of a bridge.
secondary_definitions: ( military ) A fortification around the end of a bridge .
( military ) An area of ground on the enemy 's side of a river or other obstacle , especially one that needs to be taken and defended in order to secure an advance .
( physical chemistry ) Either of the two atoms in different parts of a molecule that are connected by a bridge of two or more other atoms
